**Description**

Pearson VUE (www.pearsonvue.com) is the global leader in computer-based testing for information technology, academic, government and professional testing programs around the world. Pearson VUE provides a full suite of services from test development to data management, and delivers exams through the world’s most comprehensive and secure network of test centers in more than 180 countries, where we validate the skills and knowledge of millions of individuals every year. Pearson VUE is a business of Pearson, the world's leading learning company with global-reach and market-leading businesses.

Pearson is listed on both the London and New York stock exchanges (UK: PSON; NYSE: PSO).

Pearson VUE has an exciting opportunity for a Senior Software Product Management Analyst, (Product Manager) position.

As a Product Manager you will bridge the needs of the business to product implementation with our agile development teams. In this important role you will be responsible for providing vision and direction to the agile development team throughout the project. Ideally this is done through understanding and representing the customer to the team through backlog management, iteration planning, and elaboration of the user stories and requirements.

As a Product Manager you will be afforded the opportunity to serve as a Subject Matter Expert regarding specific products and technologies to the Product Manager team. You will be expected to make yourself available to support and mentor the team in this capacity.

In the role, you will have a chance to work closely with Business Development, Program Managers, Product Strategy and the Software Development teams as both the business requirements and functional specifications source and the business communication liaison throughout a project

**Qualifications**

**Education and Experience: **

+ Bachelor degree, preferably in a Business, Information Systems, Computer Science discipline required;

+ Related graduate degree preferred;

+ Seasoned IT or Business professional with a minimum of 3-5 years business analysis, technical experience, customer management, and/or technology implementations;

+ Significant experience with requirement elicitation, requirements documentation, and requirements management;

+ Direct customer interface experience (working with client directly on project tasks; managing client expectations);

+ Significant experience with MicroStrategy or similar data analytics/reporting tool;

+ Proven ability to quickly learn new business domains and technical applications;

+ Experience in computer-based testing, certification, and licensing industry preferred;

+ Significant experience with software development of client-server, web-based, data warehousing, reporting, or similar systems;

+ Resolves a wide range of issues in creative ways;

+ Works on issues of diverse scope where analysis of situation or data requires evaluation of a variety of factors, including an understanding of current business trends;

+ Seasoned, experienced professional with a full understanding of area of specialization;

+ Recommends improvements to policies and established procedures;

+ Strong technical thinking, analytical, and conceptualization skills;

+ Ability to provide technical alternatives, recommend solutions, and participate in implementation;

+ Ability to assimilate information and distill knowledge within time constraints;

