Reporting to the Director of Corporate Finance, the Sr. Manager of Business Analytics is a key member of Vertex’s Corporate Finance team, driving strategic use of our systems and data to enable finance and other professionals to access and leverage data into information and analyses. The Sr. Manager, Business Analytics plays a critical role in maintaining our library of reports from ERM, Hyperion, OBIEE, PowerBI, FTE and other systems/databases by ensuring that reports are complete, accurate and available for users to download. The best candidate will also triage incoming requests to ensure we maintain an appropriate library of reports and tools, evaluating new requests prior to building a new template, and steering people to the best solution for their needs. The person in this role will also endeavor to collaborate with all stakeholders to ensure quality output and standardization of documents where appropriate; he/she will work seamlessly with GIS to ensure alignment on methods, tools and priorities for VRTX and to ensure an understanding of basic system administration capabilities/requirements to be able to assist finance in determining process improvement options.

Key Responsibilities:
Build and maintain a fit-for-purpose reports library balancing customization and standardization;
Finance SME for building reports or leveraging systems to provide analytical support across the finance organization;
Corporate Finance lead for data relationship management (DRM) maintenance, making recommendations on how to add to or change data fields, leveraging best practices on reducing complexity, ensuring clear and consistent flow of information across financial systems and establishing policies/procedures as needed;
Collaborate extensively with the GIS function ensuring alignment on prioritization of and technical approach for process improvement projects, participating in creating solution roadmaps and execution of projects;
Work closely with other functions within Finance (R&D, Commercial, G&A, International) in order to understand the changing needs of those business areas and to advise on best practices for structuring data;
Anticipate internal planning / reporting needs and effectively translate business requirements into planning and reporting solutions;
Provide ad-hoc support to other Corporate Finance team members when needed;
Mentor and share expertise with all finance team members on how to maximize capabilities and usage of tools, including training as needed;
Support SOX testing and P&L flux analyses as needed.

Qualifications:
A Bachelor's degree in accounting, business, finance or data analytics
8-10 years of experience in data analytics, reporting and system administration with significant exposure to working with financial data
Proficient in working with or making sense of large and complex data sets
Proficiency with Microsoft Office Suite (especially Excel and PowerPoint)
Strong experience with multidimensional databases and business intelligence tools, experience with Oracle and Hyperion products a plus
An understanding of key financial metrics including P&L, balance sheet and cash flow calculations
Strong problem solving and analytical thinking
A demonstrated ability to be in the details without losing sight of the big picture
Strong project management capabilities as well as written and verbal communication and interpersonal skills
Proclivity to collaborate, a willingness to jump in to support the team when needed and the maturity to understand when/how to ask for help from the finance team or other SMEs
Global experience including working with foreign currencies
Questions the “as is” and has the flexibility to adapt to change – experience with lean tools / lean philosophies a plus
